  "prompt": "Is there any way to insert image/picture in nedit text editor?",
  "response": "Nedit is primarily a text editor designed for editing plain text files and does not support embedding images or rich media directly within a text document. It is focused on editing text and code rather than handling graphical content.\n\nHowever, if you're looking to reference images in a text document (for example, in a markup format like Markdown or HTML), you can do so by including the appropriate syntax to link to images. Here's how you can do it for different formats:\n\n1. **Markdown**:\n   ```markdown\n   ![Alt text](path/to/image.png)\n   ```\n\n2. **HTML**:\n   ```html\n   <img src=\"path/to/image.png\" alt=\"Alt text\">\n   ```\n\nIf you need to work with images alongside text, you might consider using a different type of editor that supports rich text or markdown, such as Markdown editors or word processors that allow image insertion.",
